        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>If after making the changes recommended in TSI-94-12-02 Revised, dated June 1994, the air
                    conditioning belt is still coming off on 8000, 9200, 9300 and 9400 Model vehicles with a Detroit
                    Diesel Series 60 engine, built before November 1995, the following change is recommended to correct
                    this condition. Replace the automatic belt tensioner (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9612091">Figure 1</hotlnk>) with a manual belt tensioner.
                </para>
                <figure id="f9612091" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9612091.webp" type="webp" resolution="150"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1.</caption>
                </figure>
                <para>This TSI letter contains parts information and service procedures to replace the automatic belt
                    tensioner with a manual belt tensioner, for the air conditioning belt on the above vehicles with a
                    Detroit Diesel Series 60 engine.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
